<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="30" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/1117</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-26">March 26, 1931</date>.<lb/>[Received April
                                15.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2381</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 2376 of March
                            24 (File No. 801.A Rublee), in which I spoke of the excellent work which
                            had <pb facs="0137" n="17" xml:id="pg_17"/> been done here by Mr.
                            Rublee, I have the honor to report that President Olaya took the
                            occasion yesterday to ask me to express to the Department of State his
                            appreciation of what Mr. Rublee had done. He said that Mr. Rublee had
                            been “more than satisfactory;” the Government was delighted with what he
                            had done, both in connection with the oil law and in connection with the
                            signing of the Barco contract.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson
                            Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>